org.jorge_rico_vivas.rust

Class Option<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jorge_rico_vivas.rust.Option<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Value type.

    public class Option<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an optional value using two states: Some if containing a value, or None if there is no value.

    This is a port and Java adaptation of the Rust's org.jorge_rico_vivas.rust.Option Type.
    Author:
    Jorge Rico Vivas

      • unwrap

        public T unwrap()
         throws java.lang.RuntimeException
        Returns the contained Some value.

        Because this function may throw a RuntimeException, its use is generally discouraged. Instead, prefer to use pattern matching and handle the None case explicitly, or call either unwrap_or or unwrap_or_else.

        Returns:
        the contained Some value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the value is None.

      • filter

        public Option<T> filter(java.util.function.Predicate<T> predicate)
        Returns None if the option is None, otherwise calls predicate with the wrapped value and returns:

        - Some(T) if predicate returns true (where T is the wrapped value). - None if predicate returns false.

        This function works similar to Rust's Iterator::filter(). You can imagine the org.jorge_rico_vivas.rust.Option<T> being an iterator over one or zero elements. filter() lets you decide which elements to keep.

        Parameters:
        predicate - Condition this Some(value) has to match in order to return itself
        Returns:
        returns this if is Some(value) and the value matches the predicate, otherwise, it returns None.

      • insert

        public T insert(T value)
        Inserts value into the option, then returns a reference to it.

        If the option already contains a value, the old value is dropped.

        See also getOrInsert, which doesn't update the value if the option already contains Some.

        Parameters:
        value - The new value.
        Returns:
        The new value.

      • getOrInsert

        public T getOrInsert(T value)

        value - The new value (if this org.jorge_rico_vivas.rust.Option is None).

      • takeIf

        public T takeIf(java.util.function.Predicate<T> predicate)
        Takes the value out of the option, but only if the predicate evaluates to true on the value.

        In other words, replaces self with None if the predicate returns true. This method operates similar to take(), but conditional.

        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate tested against the value (if Some), if true, it will take the value out of the option.
        Returns:
        Old value (If matches predicate) (Might be null).
